The paper discusses the use of automated reasoning and theory formation techniques to assist in the design of formal models, which suggests a focus on software engineering (cs.SE) and logic (cs.LO). Additionally, the use of automated techniques for exploring design alternatives and proposing suitable models suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and programming languages (cs.PL). Finally, the application of these techniques to fault analysis suggests a focus on systems and control (cs.SY).
